THREE men are due to appear in court today after a disturbance in Glasgow's South Side.A 19-year-old, a 24-year-old, and a third man were arrested in connection with the incident in Shaw Street, Govan, yesterday morning.As reported in late editions of yesterday's Evening Times, armed police and sniffer dogs swooped on a property shortly after 4am.Police cordoned off streets in the area as specialist negotiators were brought in to resolved the disturbance.All three men are expected to appear at Glasgow Sheriff Court later today.Neighbours reported hearing loud bangs, as well as shouting, coming from one of the flats in street, which is near busy Govan Road.A Police Scotland spokeswoman said: &quot;We were called to reports of a disturbance in Shaw Street, Glasgow, at around 4.15am on Tuesday.&quot;Three men have been arrested in connection with the incident and are currently detained in police custody.&quot;Emergency services, including fire crews, were called to the scene.Residents said various items were thrown from the building, including furniture, sofa cushions and piles of paper.Shards of glass were strewn across the road and pavement.One woman, who lived in a neighbouring tenement block, said she was awoken at around 4.30am by shouting.Another resident, who didn't wish to be named, said: &quot;We heard many noises, banging, shouting, screaming.&quot;But we didn't dare go out into the street to find out what was happening.&quot;Around 18 firefighters raced to the scene and were put on &quot;standby as a precaution.&quot;